@emmett9001 Sorry this took so long, but here is the work I've done to add support for lz4. It requires [lz4 Bindings for Python](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/lz4). The methods [encode_lz4_old_kafka](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/compare/master...sghaskell:feature/lz4-support?expand=1#diff-be2d15aff9900ab3baca0523701a468eR213) and [decode_lz4_old_kafka](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/compare/master...sghaskell:feature/lz4-support?expand=1#diff-be2d15aff9900ab3baca0523701a468eR244) have been borrowed from [kafka-python codec.py](https://github.com/dpkp/kafka-python/blob/a00f9ead161e8b05ac953b460950e42fa0e0b7d6/kafka/codec.py). They exist to work around the bug I discuss [here](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/issues/709#issuecomment-324156080). In order to compress without error I had to set [block_mode=1](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/compare/master...sghaskell:feature/lz4-support?expand=1#diff-be2d15aff9900ab3baca0523701a468eR192) for [independent blockmode](http://python-lz4.readthedocs.io/en/latest/lz4.frame.html?highlight=block_mode#lz4.frame.compress). 

There is little to no error handling and I have not added any tests for the code.

I was able to successfully produce and consume lz4 v0 and v1 messages in my limited testing. Have a look and give it a try.

https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.interface/issues/100

To eliminate the error, we have added below program which exclude objects from GC in the destructor in line 4.

static void
Wrapper_dealloc(Wrapper *self)
{
  PyObject_GC_UnTrack((PyObject *)self); //Add this line to eliminate self from GC
  Wrapper_clear(self);
  self->ob_type->tp_free((PyObject*)self);
}

[zope.interface.zip](https://github.com/zopefoundation/zope.interface/files/1301445/zope.interface.zip)

